    <h1>The Ultimate Super Bowl Experience: A Complete Guide to America's Biggest Sporting Spectacle</h1>

    <h2>Pre-Game Traditions</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <strong>The Ultimate Spread</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Mountains of wings (Americans consume over 1.4 billion on Super Bowl Sunday)</li>
                <li>Pizza deliveries reach their yearly peak</li>
                <li>Guacamole becomes liquid gold (about 80 million pounds consumed)</li>
                <li>The sacred seven-layer dip makes its annual appearance</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>The Setup Ritual</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Strategic couch positioning for optimal viewing</li>
                <li>The great debate over seat assignments</li>
                <li>Setting up multiple screens for social media commentary</li>
                <li>Laying out the snack stadium</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>During the Game</h2>
    <ol start="3">
        <li>
            <strong>Commercial Breaks: The Other Main Event</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Entire rooms falling silent for $7 million, 30-second spots</li>
                <li>Rating each ad's creativity and humor</li>
                <li>Anticipating which brands will create the next viral moment</li>
                <li>Debating which commercial deserves the unofficial "best ad" crown</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Halftime Show Spectacle</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>The mass exodus to refill plates</li>
                <li>Impromptu living room dance parties</li>
                <li>Critiquing the performance like seasoned music producers</li>
                <li>Comparing it to legendary shows of years past</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Game Day Superstitions</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Lucky jerseys that haven't been washed since '85</li>
                <li>Specific seating arrangements that "ensure" team victory</li>
                <li>Rally caps for comeback attempts</li>
                <li>The "don't move, it's working" freeze</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Party Elements</h2>
    <ol start="6">
        <li>
            <strong>The Pools and Bets</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Square pools for each quarter</li>
                <li>Prop bets on everything imaginable</li>
                <li>First touchdown predictions</li>
                <li>National anthem length timing</li>
                <li>Coin toss calling rights</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>The Cast of Characters</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>The Statistics Guru who knows every player's history</li>
                <li>The Commercial Critic who works in marketing</li>
                <li>The Once-a-Year Football Fan who asks endless questions</li>
                <li>The Chef who takes the snack spread too seriously</li>
                <li>The Referee who argues every call</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Technical Traditions</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Testing the TV setup hours before kickoff</li>
                <li>The panic when the stream buffers</li>
                <li>Backup viewing options ready</li>
                <li>The annual struggle with surround sound settings</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Post-Game Rituals</h2>
    <ol start="9">
        <li>
            <strong>The Aftermath</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Monday morning quarterbacks</li>
                <li>Next-day food coma</li>
                <li>The great cleanup operation</li>
                <li>Social media deep dives into memes and highlights</li>
                <li>Planning for "next year"</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>The Legacy Elements</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Saving commemorative cups and plates</li>
                <li>Updating personal record books of parties hosted</li>
                <li>Collecting betting pool winnings</li>
                <li>Archiving photos of the epic spread</li>
                <li>Adding to the running list of "remember when" moments</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>The New Standards</h2>
    <ol start="11">
        <li>
            <strong>Social Media Integration</strong>
            <ul>
